# Force text-mode handling on source extensions that should never be
# classified as binary.
#
# Why: git's auto-detection samples the first few KB of a file and
# flags it as binary on the presence of certain byte patterns. TS
# files with non-ASCII characters in doc comments — em dashes, curly
# quotes, the kind of typography pino-pretty / docs editors emit —
# can trip that heuristic. The visible failure mode is a squash-merge
# that silently produces a 0-byte file because GitHub falls back to
# "take theirs" on a "binary" file rather than performing the
# expected per-line merge.
#
# We hit this on `runtimes/typescript/src/openapi/schemas.ts` when
# the squash of #223 zeroed the file in main. The hotfix in #224
# reconstructed the file; this entry stops it from happening again
# (on any file matched below).
#
# Scope is intentionally narrow: only the source extensions we
# actually edit. We deliberately do NOT use `* text=auto` here — that
# would normalize line endings across the whole repo on next
# checkout, which is too broad a change for the problem we're
# solving. Adding extensions is fine; just append below.

*.ts text
*.tsx text
*.js text
*.jsx text
*.mjs text
*.cjs text
*.json text
*.md text
*.mdx text
*.yaml text
*.yml text
*.css text
*.html text
*.toml text
*.sh text
*.py text
*.java text
*.kt text
*.gradle text
*.kts text
